      "writtenOn": "2026-03-10T11:23:24Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "We have single consul snap, that is used to deploy either consul server or consul client depending upon the input config passed. https://github.com/canonical/snap-consul/blob/main/snap-wrappers/consul-wrapper#L6C68-L7C108\n\nSo that is why, consul-client-operator charm https://github.com/canonical/consul-client-operator builds the socket path with in charm, prepare the config, then start the snap with that config. \n\nRegarding slot, hypervisor defines `hypervisor/\u003csocket name\u003e`\n\nOn the plug side, consul-client defines plug target path which is currently SNAP_DATA, the slot `hypervisor/\u003csocket name\u003e` is mounted as is in SNAP_DATA so consumer becomes   `SNAP_DATA/hypervisor/\u003csocket name\u003e`",
      "parentUuid": "18e91b55_6a820fd0",
